I just wanted the tacos I ordered or even a refund for those items, but they instead chose to treat me with total disrespect, telling me lies about DoorDash that I easily disproved with a google search. I decided to order from here for the first time yesterday, and it will be my last. I ordered shrimp nachos and got the blandest tasting Mexican dish I've ever had. The tortilla chips were too thin, half soggy, almost stale, and had NO flavor. Same goes for the beans, cheese, guacamole, and the rest of the toppings when it came to flavor. I'm not exaggerating when I say that it is the blandest Mexican food I've ever had. The shrimp just tasted like it was already pre cooked and came straight from a freezer bag. The only thing that made this dish halfway decent was the green salsa that I had to purchase on the side for extra. Even though the salsa had an ok flavor, it was still very watery and not even close to authentic Mexican salsa. I am from Texas, and I've had similar mediocre food before. Fiesta Cafe most definitely ranks highest on the list of Mexican food establishments that I will never eat at again.
